main event: An unidentified aerial phenomenon was sighted that appeared to stop and then resume movement.
interesting points: The object appeared to have 2 or more lights and was visible for about 3 to 5 minutes,The object would appear and disappear several times,No radar contact was obtained with the object,It was described as being sharply defined, like a larger star,The sighting occurred under heavy seas with weather conditions generally clear but with intermittent showers.
sighted object: one round object resembling Venus with lights
witness description: highly reliable Navy personnel, including a pilot and navigator
